<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-01-15T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-01-15T23:00:00-05:00" n="812" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d812">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/653: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-16T12:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">January 16,
                                        1926—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received January 16—6:09
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. My telegram number 25, January 14, 10 a.m. I am reliably informed
                            that Japanese Minister addressed to the Chinese Government, January
                            14th, a note protesting against transaction of commercial business with
                            France by French wireless station at Yünnanfu, and with Germany by
                            station at Mukden, reasserting claim to 30-year monopoly.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>